## Documentation & Commit History

- **Update Documentation:** If your changes affect project structure, components, APIs, etc., update the corresponding file in `docs/`.
- **Use GitHub for History:** This project uses the Git commit history as the changelog. Refer to `docs/GITHUB_GUIDELINES.md` for conventions.
- **Write Good Commits:** Write clear, descriptive commit messages following the Conventional Commits standard. The commit message is the primary source of information about a change.

## Important Gotchas

- Astro components are server-only by default - use `<script>` tag for client-side interactivity
- Base URL must be used for all internal links and API calls
- Brevo sender email MUST be verified in dashboard before emails can be sent
- ESLint uses v9 flat config format - don't revert to old format

